  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Somalia Joint Justice Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To develop action plans at local level through inclusive community dialogue on justice and security issues, that inform the support for institutional strengthening, federalization of the justice sector, financial sustainability and the establishment of accountability mechanisms. 2) To strengthen the capacity of key justice institutions to deliver on the priorities identified in the community dialogue.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Alternative Dispute Resolution Centers, Ministry of Justice, Attorney General&apos;s Office (AGO), Sexual and Gender-Based Violence Unit at the AGO, Somali Bar Association. Indirect beneficiaries: Citizens of Somalia</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The program aimed to contribute to sustainable security, peace and development by strengthening justice institutions to deliver professional and standardized justice services to communities, particularly women, children and internally displaced persons (IDPs), and guarantee better protection of individuals&#x2019; rights.</narrative>
  </description>
